{"ID":270306, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"306\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs305.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs307.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 306<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">tabernacles, then died and again have risen and received glorified bodies, they will have an\n  ascendency over the spirits who have received no bodies, or kept not their first estate,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> like the devil.\n  The punishment of the devil was that he should not have a habitation like men.<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> The devil&rsquo;s\n  retaliation is, he comes into this world, binds up men&rsquo;s bodies, and occupies them himself.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> When\n  the authorities come along, they eject him from a stolen habitation.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The design of the great God in sending us into this world,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and organizing us to prepare us for\n  the eternal worlds, I shall keep in my own bosom at present.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">We have no claim in our eternal compact, in relation to eternal things, unless our actions and\n  contracts<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> and all things tend to this. But after all this, you have got to make your calling and election\n  sure.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> If this injunction would lie largely on those to whom it was spoken, how much more those of\n  the present generation!<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">1st key: Knowledge<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> is the power of salvation.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> 2nd key: Make your calling and election sure.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span>\n  3rd key: It is one thing to be on the mount and hear the excellent voice,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> etc., and another to hear\n  the voice declare to you, You have a part and lot in that kingdom.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> (May 21, 1843.) DHC\n  5:401-403.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Prophet on Forming Temperance Societies<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Dear Brother:&mdash;In answer to yours of May 4th, concerning the Latter-day Saints forming a\n  temperance society, we would say, as Paul said&mdash;&ldquo;Be not unequally yoked with unbelievers,<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> but\n  contend for the faith once delivered to the Saints&rdquo;;<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> and as Peter advises, so say we,<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">&ldquo;Add to your knowledge, temperance.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> As Paul said he had to become all things to all men,\n  that he might thereby save some,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> so must the elders of the last days do; and, being sent out to\n  preach the Gospel<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and warn the world of the judgments<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> to come, we are sure, when they teach\n  as directed by the Spirit,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> according to the revelations<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> of Jesus Christ,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> that they will preach the\n  truth<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> and prosper without complaint. Thus we have no new commandment to give, but admonish\n  elders and members<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> to live by every word that proceedeth forth from the mouth of God,<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> lest they\n  come short of the glory<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> that is reserved for the faithful.<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> (May 22, 1843.) DHC 5:404.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117057\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117057)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117057)\">Abr. 3:28<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"105975\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 105975)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(105975)\">Gen. 3:15<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116765\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116765)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116765)\">Moses 4:21<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112273\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112273)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112273)\">Alma 40:13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107918\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107918)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107918)\">Matt. 9:33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108340\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108340)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108340)\">Mark 7:26-30<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116736\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116736)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116736)\">Moses 1:31,39<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116334\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116334)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116334)\">D&amp;C 132:7,13-16,19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110515\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110515)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110515)\">2 Pet. 1:10<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108512\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108512)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108512)\">Luke 11:53 (JST)<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <s